Business Brief -- Campbell Soup Co.:
   Fiscal Second-Quarter Net
   Rose 19% as Sales Fell 1.4%
Operating profit at Campbell North America rose 18% to
$261.1 million, while sales rose 2% to $1.25 billion, it
said. Unit sales of soup increased 6%, primarily because of
the acquisition of Sanwa Foods Inc., a ramen noodle maker,
and introduction of the Healthy Request soup line.
   At the biscuit and bakery unit, operating profit fell 5%
to $24.9 million, while sales rose 4% to $216.5 million from
$208.3 million.
   In the first half, net rose 21% to $289.8 million, or
$1.15 a share, from $240.4 million, or 95 cents a share, a
year earlier. Sales declined 2.1% to $3.29 billion from $3.37
billion.